<div class="what-is-logicly">
  <h2>What is Logicly?</h2>
  <%= image_tag("photo/iconic-shot-of-earth.jpg") %>
  <p>
    A Platform for discovery and learning
    <br /><br />
    It is a social discussion and consensus platform where you can participate with others, 
    discussing topics in the <a {{action scroll_to '#idea-base'}}>Idea Base</a> and 
    <a {{action scroll_to '#link-base'}}>Link Base</a>.
  </p>
</div>

<section class="signup-section top-signup-section">
  <h2>Interested in inspiring others with your ideas?</h2>
  <div>
    <center>
      {{view App.ErrorsView errors=errors}}
      {{input type="text" placeholder="Your email address" spellcheck="false" autocomplete="off" valueBinding=email}}
      <button {{action "submit"}} {{bind-attr disabled=disabled}}>Join the Logicly Beta Now</button>
    </center>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="special-hr"></div>

<section class="dual-content">
  <h2 class="hidden-on-mobile">Sharing ideas is what Logicly is all about</h2>
  <div class="bases">
    <div id="idea-base">
      <center><%= image_tag("photo/lightbulb-sprout.png") %></center>
      <h3>What is the Idea Base?</h3>
      <p>
        The Idea Base is an encyclopedia-like, user-maintained database of ideas you want to 
        discuss. Whether that idea is a controversial theory or an interesting question, 
        anything is open for discussion.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div id="link-base">
      <center><%= image_tag("photo/www.png") %></center>
      <h3>What is the Link Base?</h3>
      <p>
        The Link Base is a database of user-submitted links to any page around the web you want
        to discuss. Whether that link is a YouTube video with disabled ratings and comments or 
        a controversial tweet, anything is open for discussion.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="special-hr"></div>

<section class="dual-content">
  <h2 class="hidden-on-mobile">Discussion on Logicly is easy with our Discussion Platform</h2>
  <div class="bases discussion">
    <div>
      <h3>What is the Discussion Platform?</h3>
      <p>
        The discussion platform is a place where you can submit comments and vote on the best 
        ones for or against a topic.
        <br /><br />
        The power of Logicly's platform comes from our focus on opposing viewpoints. You're able 
        to view both sides of an argument side-by-side, deciding which opinions are the best. The 
        most popular opinions in each viewpoint rise to the top.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="has-img">
      <center><%= image_tag("photo/discussion.jpg") %></center>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="special-hr no-margin"></div>

<section class="dual-content">
  <h2 class="hidden-on-mobile">We are building a place where everyone can discover and learn</h2>
  <div class="bases in-beta">
    <div>
      <center>
        <span>
          <a href="https://twitter.com/2logicly" target="_BLANK">
            <%= image_tag("icons/webicon-twitter.svg") %>
          </a>
          <a href="https://plus.google.com/u/5/b/107502998479803230755/107502998479803230755/about" target="_BLANK">
            <%= image_tag("icons/webicon-googleplus.svg", :class => "with-margin") %>
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/2Logicly" target="_BLANK">
            <%= image_tag("icons/webicon-facebook.svg", :class => "with-margin") %>
          </a>
        </span>
      </center>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>When can you use Logicly?</h3>
      <p>
        Logicly is under active development and we plan to launch the Beta soon. If you sign up for 
        the Beta below, we will let you know when it's ready. You can help spread the word by sharing 
        our website and social networks. Follow us on twitter or any of our other social fronts to keep 
        up to date on Logicly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="special-hr"></div>

<section class="signup-section bottom-signup-section">
  <h2>Ready to help others understand the world?</h2>
  <div>
    <center>
      {{view App.ErrorsView errors=errors}}
      {{input type="text" placeholder="Your email address" spellcheck="false" autocomplete="off" valueBinding=email}}
      <button {{action "submit"}} {{bind-attr disabled=disabled}}>Join the Logicly Beta Now</button>
    </center>
  </div>
</section>